title: M6 southbound reopens after crash
text:
A motorcyclist was trapped under a car on the M6 this morning. Credit: West Midlands Ambulance The M6 southbound carriageway has reopened after a major crash, which saw a motorcyclist trapped underneath a car.
The crash happened between J6 (Spaghetti Junction) and J5 (Castle Bromwich) at around 7am this morning. There is congestion back to J9 (Wednesbury).
